{
  "stem": "14897.4",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So my father ministered as much as he could to the sick in our group.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And he--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Only our group.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Our group was privileged in another way.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "At the beginning, the-- the people who were our official representatives with the Germans were the-- the Jewish Gestapo, who, of course, continued-- this-- this was customary in-- in German camps.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And you probably know the name kapo, which is a sort of a-- a-- a-- a-- like a foreman, you know, an inmate of the camp who led the privileged life and who was usually absolutely the dregs of society, because he was willing to-- to-- to keep his life better by oppressing his own people.",
      "word_count": 56
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We asked the-- the German, which was very risky, the German commander of the camp-- I think his name was Hess, H-E-S-S, one of those people who was later in the Nuremberg Trials-- if he would allow us to pick our own representative and govern ourselves.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And again, he was intrigued by it and permitted it, so that our leader became a wonderful man and engineer who spoke beautiful, perfect German.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "His name was Solowiejczik, S-O-L-O-W-I-E-J-C-Z-I-K.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And within our group, we were governed in a very fair way.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "For example, you know, when a group works together, it can be better for everybody.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We would-- he would, for example, negotiate with the German guards to get some milk or some other food, which we would deprive ourselves of so the children would have it or the sick people.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And it gave us a sense of being human.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "One of the things that happened to people in camps is-- it's the same psychology as slaves in the United States.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "When you're oppressed enough, many people believe that you deserve it.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
